# Naming Conventions

## Feature Hooks (Client)

Use descriptive, use-case focused names:

```typescript
// List query with options/filters
export function useItems(options?: {
  userId?: string;
  categoryId?: string;
  status?: string;
  search?: string;
});

// Usage examples:
// useItems()                              → all items
// useItems({ userId: 'user_123' })        → items for specific user
// useItems({ categoryId: 'cat_456' })     → items in category
// useItems({ userId: 'me', status: 'draft' }) → filtered by user and status

// Single item
export function useItem(id: string);

// Mutations
export function useCreateItem();
export function useUpdateItem();
export function useDeleteItem();
```

**Note:** Define options/filter types in `types.ts` for reuse across hooks and queries.

## Feature Queries (Server)

Mirror Convex naming with `get` prefix:

```typescript
// queries.ts - Server reads
export async function getItems();
export async function getItem(id);
export async function getMyItems();
export async function getItemsByCategory(categoryId);
```

## Feature Actions (Server)

Mirror Convex naming with verb prefix:

```typescript
// actions.ts - Server writes
export async function createItem(data);
export async function updateItem(id, data);
export async function deleteItem(id);
export async function publishItem(id);
export async function archiveItem(id);
```

## Convex Functions

### Query Functions

```typescript
// Describe the data operation
export const list = query(...)
export const get = query(...)
export const getBySlug = query(...)
export const search = query(...)
```

### Mutation Functions

```typescript
// Use action verbs
export const create = mutation(...)
export const update = mutation(...)
export const remove = mutation(...)    // Use "remove" instead of "delete"
export const toggle = mutation(...)
export const publish = mutation(...)
export const archive = mutation(...)
```

## Service Functions

### Auth Service

```typescript
// client.ts
export function useSession();
export function signIn(credentials);
export function signOut();

// server.ts
export async function getServerSession();
export async function requireAuth();
```

### Email Service

```typescript
// server.ts
export async function sendEmail(to, subject, body);
export async function sendWelcomeEmail(user);
export async function sendResetPasswordEmail(user);
```

### Analytics Service

```typescript
// client.ts
export function trackEvent(name, properties);
export function trackPageView(path);

// server.ts
export async function trackServerEvent(name, properties);
```

## Utility Functions

Use clear, descriptive names:

```typescript
// date.ts
export function formatDate(date);
export function formatRelativeTime(date);

// string.ts
export function capitalize(str);
export function slugify(str);

// array.ts
export function groupBy<T>(arr, key);
export function unique<T>(arr);
```

## Type Naming

```typescript
// types.ts
export type Item = {...}
export type ItemWithRelations = {...}
export type CreateItemInput = {...}
export type UpdateItemInput = {...}

// Avoid generic names
// ❌ Bad
export type Data = {...}
export type Props = {...}

// ✅ Good
export type ItemData = {...}
export type ItemCardProps = {...}
```

## Constants

Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for true constants:

```typescript
// constants.ts
export const MAX_ITEMS_PER_USER = 100;
export const DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE = 20;
export const API_BASE_URL = 'https://api.example.com';
```

Use camelCase for configuration objects:

```typescript
// config.ts
export const authConfig = {
  providers: [...],
  session: {...},
};
```

## File Naming

Use consistent patterns:

```typescript
// Features
lib / features / items / hooks.ts;
lib / features / items / queries.ts;
lib / features / items / actions.ts;
lib / features / items / types.ts;
lib / features / items / validation.ts;
lib / features / items / utils.ts;

// Services
lib / services / auth / client.ts;
lib / services / auth / server.ts;
lib / services / auth / config.ts;

// Utils
lib / utils / date.ts;
lib / utils / string.ts;
lib / utils / array.ts;
```

## Best Practices

### Avoid Abbreviations

```typescript
// ❌ Unclear
export function getItms();
export function useItm();

// ✅ Clear
export function getItems();
export function useItem();
```

### Be Consistent

Within a feature, use consistent naming patterns:

```typescript
// ✅ Consistent
export function useItems(); // List
export function useItem(id); // Single
export function useCreateItem(); // Mutation

// ❌ Inconsistent
export function useItems();
export function getItem(id);
export function createNewItem();
```

### Context Matters

File provides context, avoid redundancy:

```typescript
// In items/hooks.ts
// ❌ Redundant
export function useItemsList();
export function useItemsGet();

// ✅ Concise
export function useItems();
export function useItem();
```
